From gloster Vance Gloster Subject Re Compositing pictures on PC In article chu Patrick Chu writes I was wondering if anyone knows of a graphics package for the PC that will do compositing of a series of pictures What I mean by compositing is say I have a live video clip digitized panning around a living room and a computer generated bird flying around the I want to combine these two series of pictures so that everywhere where the bird frames are black I want the living room picture to show Yes I realize I can do this with a genlock and I do own a genlock but I want to be able to do manual compositing It's ok if I have to composite one frame at a time I assumed I'd have to do that But being able to composite a series of frames would be even I've looked around and I haven't found a PC package that will perform Help please If you can get the live animation and the computer generated animation into AutoDesk Animator or format AutoDesk Animator will do this for It can take one animation make a certain color clear and overlay it over another I do not have a way right now to convert or files to animator Animator will also import a series of files to create an animation so if your video capture stuff can create this is might Vance Gloster